# Telegram Bot - Administrator Guide

## Quick Start

### Starting the Bot
```bash
cd Server
node Bot/telegram_bot.js
```

Or use the existing deployment method (render.com, etc.)

## Configuration

### Environment Variables Required
```env
TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN=your_bot_token_here
MONGODB_URI=mongodb://localhost:27017/karur_hms
Gemi_Api_Key=your_gemini_api_key (optional)
```

## Managing Doctors

### Ensure Doctors Are Active
The bot only shows **active** doctors. Make sure doctors have:
```javascript
{
  role: 'doctor',
  is_active: true,
  firstName: 'John',
  lastName: 'Doe',
  metadata: {
    specialization: 'Cardiologist',  // or
    department: 'Cardiology'
  }
}
```

### Adding Doctor Specializations
Update doctor records to include specialization:
```javascript
await User.findByIdAndUpdate(doctorId, {
  $set: {
    'metadata.specialization': 'Gastroenterologist',
    'metadata.department': 'Gastroenterology'
  }
});
```

